&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12572006" author="udanax" created="Mon, 25 Feb 2008 02:42:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t say that you can enabling/disabling/dropping tables by each command.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12572010" author="bryanduxbury" created="Mon, 25 Feb 2008 03:33:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems like nice additions. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Few comments:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I assume enable/disable all just offlines user tables, not root and meta?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The help for enable should probably be something like &quot;Put a table or tables online&quot;, and disable should be &quot;Take a table or tables offline&quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Should we actually allow &quot;drop all&quot;? It seems very risky to let a user indiscriminately blow away all the tables in their database. Maybe add an &quot;are you sure&quot; prompt or something? Probably not a big deal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s fix the help for enable/disable and then we&apos;ll get this committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12573947" author="bryanduxbury" created="Fri, 29 Feb 2008 20:45:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Edward - are you planning to address my comments on this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12574323" author="udanax" created="Mon, 3 Mar 2008 01:42:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Maybe add an &quot;are you sure&quot; prompt or something?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sounds good. I&apos;ll upload a v02 patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
